description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian announced that his administration is poised to take significant steps to bolster relations with Oman.
title: Iran set to enhance relations with Oman: Pezeshkian

description: TEHRAN-The Iranian documentary “Foreboding,” also known as “Molf-e Gand,” directed by Mahmoud Rahmani was screened at the University of Illinois in the U.S. on Saturday.
title: University of Illinois screens Iranian documentary “Foreboding”

description: TEHRAN-The Iranian drama film “Fear and Trembling” written and directed by Manijeh Hekmat and Faezeh Azizkhani will have its world premiere at the 55th International Film Festival of India (IFFI) running from November 20 to 28, in Goa, India.
title: 55th International Film Festival of India picks Iranian film for main competition

description: TEHRAN – During a two-day regional visit, Iran's Defense Minister Brigadier General Aziz Nasirzadeh engaged with several senior Syrian officials, culminating in a meeting with President Bashar al-Assad on Sunday.
title: Syria key to Iran’s foreign policy, DM says in Damascus visit

description: TEHRAN-A classical concert will be held at the Roudaki Hall in Tehran on November 18 and 19, where 10 pieces by the famous German composer and musician Johann Sebastian Bach will be performed.
title: Roudaki Hall to host “Johann Sebastian Bach Night”

description: TEHRAN – Following over a year of Israeli violence in Gaza, Lebanon, Syria, and the West Bank, hundreds of Iranian Sunni scholars are urging fellow religious leaders across the Arab world and beyond to issue fatwas supporting Palestine.
title: Iranian Sunni scholars urge fatwas for Palestine

description: For Democratic pro-Palestinian activists, Donald Trump’s reelection delivered a bitter vindication.
title: ‘Blame yourself’: Trump’s election hasn’t dampened pro-Palestine activists’ anger at Democrats

description: MADRID – According to various international policy experts, Donald Trump’s first term was characterized by a nationalist approach aimed at strengthening the independence of the United States and reducing its reliance on traditional allies.
title: The road ahead: Iran, Israel, and the Persian Gulf in Trump's foreign policy

description: TEHRAN – The Iranian Parliament’s National Security and Foreign Policy Committee has convened to address critical issues surrounding the country’s nuclear program, the visit by International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) Director General Rafael Grossi, and support for Iranians living abroad.
title: Details of IAEA chief’s visit inquired by Iran's parliament as MPs call for 'reciprocal measures’

description: Tehran – A bid to scrap a pending bill barring dual nationals from holding key government positions in Iran was decisively rejected by the parliament on Saturday.
title: Iranian parliament upholds ban on dual nationals in key government roles

description: MADRID – Various U.S. and international media outlets have reported that Marco Rubio could be appointed as the next Secretary of State in Donald Trump's administration. This would place him at the helm of U.S. foreign policy, with the responsibility of managing international relations and safeguarding the country's geopolitical interests.
title: Marco Rubio poised for US Secretary of State, promising a tougher approach on Iran

description: TEHRAN - Hezbollah has responded to the Israeli regime’s heavy bombardment of the Lebanese capital Beirut’s southern suburb.
title: Hezbollah sends Haifa into the dark

description: TEHRAN- Germany is among certain Western countries that stands accused of aiding and abetting the Israeli genocidal war on Gaza.
title: Gaza burning, Germany beaming

description: TEHRAN- Israel’s killing machine operates relentlessly in Lebanon as more civilians and officials fall victim to the regime’s airstrikes.
title: Israeli strike kills Hezbollah media chief

description: BEIRUT - Despite relentless concentrated bombardments on Lebanon, all attempts by Israeli invaders have failed to make ground advances.
title: Will Hochstein’s tour of Lebanon stop the aggression?

description: TEHRAN- The recent firing of a pair of flares at Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's private residence in Caesarea has highlighted growing divisions among Israeli officials.
title: Flares and fallout: Israeli officials lock horns over military failures

description: TEHRAN – In a televised interview on Saturday, Iran's Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi issued a stark warning to the Israeli regime regarding the consequences of any further aggression against Iran, particularly targeting its nuclear facilities.
title: Araghchi warns Israel against further aggression as Iran gears up for retaliation

description: TEHRAN - In a note, the Iran newspaper discussed the 100 days of the arduous path of the Pezeshkian government and quoted former diplomat Abbas Mousavi as saying: The terrorist operation that took place at the beginning of the government of Mr. Pezeshkian by the Zionist regime created a situation that affected the foreign policy and led to immediate actions by the government.
title: Special diplomatic moves in 100 fateful days

description: TEHRAN – The Islamic Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC) has inaugurated a state-of-the-art wargaming center at its University of Command and Staff located in Tehran.
title: IRGC opens cutting-edge military simulation center

description: TEHRAN- “Thelma”, a 2024 comedy movie directed by American director Josh Margolin, will go on screen at the Andisheh Cultural Center in Tehran on Monday.
title: Andisheh cultural center to review “Thelma”

description: TEHRAN- The world-renowned Iranian filmmaker Abbas Kiarostami’s 1974 film “The Traveler” is on screen at the 46th edition of Festival des 3 Continents (Three Continents Film Festival), which is currently underway in Nantes, France.
title: Kiarostami’s “Traveler” on screen at Festival des 3 Continents

description: TEHRAN - Iran national football team, despite topping Group A in the AFC Asian Qualifiers - Road to 26  World Cup, have faced growing scrutiny following their recent performance against North Korea.
title: Fans dissatisfied with Iran football performance

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s football team defeated the U.S. 3-0 in the 2024 Cerebral Palsy World Cup underway in Salou, Spain on Sunday.
title: Iran to play Brazil at 2024 Cerebral Palsy World Cup sf

description: TEHRAN – Moslem Shojaei, the director of marketing and foreign tourism development at Iran’s Ministry of Cultural Heritage, Tourism, and Handicrafts, has announced promising outcomes from Iran’s recent tourism roadshow held in Sulaymaniyah, the Kurdistan Region of Iraq.
title: Flights between Sanandaj, Kurdistan Region of Iraq proposed to strengthen tourism

description: TEHRAN - FIFA President Gianni Infantino has spotlighted a humble yet spirited village football field in Iran, capturing the hearts of football enthusiasts worldwide.
title: FIFA president highlights football field in northern Iranian village

description: TEHRAN – Sanat Mes of Iran defeated Al Duhail of Qatar 27-26 at the 27th Asian Men’s Club League Handball Championship on Sunday.
title: Mes edge Al Duhail in Asian Club League Handball Championship

description: TEHRAN - Nestled in the serene garden in the ancient city of Neyshabur, the Kamal-ol-Molk mausoleum stands as a tribute to one of Iran’s most celebrated contemporary artists, Mohammad Ghaffari, known as Kamal-ol-Molk (1224–1319).
title: Kamal-ol-Molk mausoleum: a masterpiece of Persian art and architecture

description: TEHRAN - Fatemeh Mohajerani, the spokesperson for the Iranian government, has emphasized the importance of handicrafts as a cornerstone of national development during her visit to the 37th National Handicraft Exhibition in Tehran on Saturday.
title: Government spokesperson underlines handicrafts’ role in national development

description: TEHRAN – President Masoud Pezeshkian referred to the government's prioritization of the maritime-oriented economy and the importance of the prosperity of this sector on the country's growth, development and prosperity, and stated that the government is determined to implement maritime-oriented development plans.
title: Pezeshkian emphasizes prioritizing maritime-oriented economy in development plans
